ert it is processed without restarting daemon.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.0,"Integration":0.08,"System":0.92,"Agentic":0.0,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"When multiple files arrive at the same time, they are processed in the order determined by their creation timestamps.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"MOCK-MISS: ordering depends on handoff among watcher events, metadata reads, and scheduler/queue. REAL-INFRA/MOCK-HIDE: real filesystem timestamp precision/availability and concurrent arrival timing can differ from mocks; mocked metadata can hide incorrect real ordering behavior. Rejection-gate: I considered Integration, but rejected it because the behavior is specifically about simultaneously arriving files and ordering by filesystem creation timestamps, which requires real filesystem timing/metadata behavior.","test_description":"Create multiple files near-simultaneously in watched directory, capture processing order from daemon logs/hooks, and assert order matches actual creation timestamps read from filesystem.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.04,"Integration":0.26,"System":0.7,"Agentic":0.0,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":6,"description":"A file that is still being written to when the arrival event fires is not picked up for processing until writing is complete.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"MOCK-MISS: failure appears in interaction between real write-in-progress behavior and pickup/readiness logic. REAL-INFRA/MOCK-HIDE: partial writes, flush timing, and event timing are OS/filesystem realities; stubs often present fully written content immediately. Rejection-gate: I considered Integration, but rejected it because the behavior explicitly depends on file still being written when event fires, a real filesystem timing condition.","test_description":"Write a file in chunks with delays while daemon runs; assert daemon do